# Make an alias, facet_var, for original name
df <- mutate(df, facet_var = paste(original_name, "and variants"))

pareto_data <- filter(df, dominant == TRUE)
natural_data <- filter(df, natural == TRUE)

# Careful, this is incorrect.
variants_data <- filter(df, str_detect(name, "_variant_"))

# Be careful, this might not always be the case
naturals_and_variants_df <- bind_rows(natural_data, variants_data)
plot = (
  # Set data and the axes
  ggplot(
    data=natural_data, # set for faceting
    mapping=aes(x=complexity, y=comm_cost),
  )
  # + scale_y_continuous(limits=[0, 1])
  + geom_line(data=pareto_data)
  + geom_point(  # naturals and variants
      data=naturals_and_variants_df,
      stroke=0,
      # alpha=.5,
      mapping=aes(
        color=original_name,
        shape=dp_restricted,
      ),
      size=4,
  )
  + geom_point( # natural langs
    data=natural_data,
    shape="+",
    size=8,
  )
  + geom_text_repel(
    data=natural_data,
    mapping=aes(label=name),
    size=6,
    nudge_x=1,
  )
  + scale_color_discrete()
  + theme_classic()
)
plot

(
  # Set data and the axes
  ggplot(
    mapping=aes(x=complexity, y=comm_cost),
  )
  # + scale_y_continuous(limits=[0, 1])
  + geom_line(
    # remove faceting variable here so it is present in facet_wrap
    data=select(pareto_data, -facet_var),
  )
  + geom_point(  # all langs
      data=naturals_and_variants_df,
      stroke=0,
      alpha=.3,
      mapping=aes(
        # color=original_name,
        color=dp_restricted,
        shape=dp_restricted,
      ),
      size=3,
  )
  + geom_point( # natural langs
    data=natural_data,
    shape="+",
    size=8,
  )
  # Annotate originals
  + geom_text_repel(
    data=natural_data,
    mapping=aes(label=name),
    size=4,
    nudge_x=2,
  )  
  
  + facet_wrap(vars(facet_var))
  
  + scale_color_discrete()
  # + theme_classic()
)

ggsave(
  "faceted_langs.png",
  width=10,
  height=10,
)
